  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "As documented in https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/configuration/best_practices/level_two, @alyssawilk and I have discussed forcing the user to specify an HCM configuration option that specifies how to handle stream errors, thus guiding users into selecting the correct option for their use case. I think the best way of doing this is:\r\n1) Add a new option to configure this setting using a bool WKT, deprecate the old option, and explicitly warn/stat if the new option is not set at all, telling the user that in a future version this setting will be required.\r\n2) In the normal \"deprecation cycle\" make the new setting required.",
